Futuregrowth has agreed to lift the suspension on lending with immediate effect subject to agreed improvements. JOHANNESBURG - The Development Bank of South Africa says asset manager Futuregrowth has agreed to lift suspension on lending with immediate effect subject to agreed improvements and additional reporting.This follows the conclusion of a rigorous due diligence process during which Futuregrowth reviewed the DBSA s governance structures processes and independence.On 31 August asset manager pulled the plug on R 1.8 billion worth of loans to state-owned entities due to governance concernsFuturegrowth has also lifted its suspension against the Land Bank and the Industrial Development Corporation.(Edited by Neo Koza)